                <h1>Does Marriage Appear on Background Checks?</h1>
                <p>Marriage can show up on a background check depending on the depth of the investigation. Background checks often include public records, which may list marital status and any associated legal documents, like marriage certificates or name changes. However, the extent of this information may vary by service and jurisdiction.</p>
